OL,7,FNearly half of over-65s in England are
OL,8,Ftaking at least five different
OL,9,Fmedications a day. Meanwhile, a third
OL,10,Fof the same age group experience at
OL,11,Fleast one fall a year.
OL,13,FExperts think the two statistics are
OL,14,Flinked and that a rapid growth in
OL,15,F"poly-pharmacy" is creating new health
OL,16,Fhazards for older people.
OL,18,FTheir prescribed drugs can interact
OL,19,Fwith each other to cause additional
OL,20,Fside effects such as dizziness and
OL,21,Fconfusion that can lead to falls.
OL,3,CHow a 'virtual pharmacist' could cut
OL,4,Cthe risk of dangerous falls for elderly
